VArtificial and Natural Intelligence
p918
sg9
VWhat is intelligence? An inquiry into the nature of intelligence can take different forms \u2013 philosophical, biological, mathematical or technological. In this Freshman Seminar, we will use machine intelligence (everything from voice recognizing smartphones to Jeopardy-playing computers) as a handle to think about natural intelligence (brains and behavior of animals). Although we will start with big, general questions, we will quickly move to concrete queries about brains and computers. This approach, rather than just starting with brains of animals, may be useful in framing more universal questions independent of the specific architecture of brains of animals. This seminar targets students that are interested in brains and computers in equal measure, and are comfortable with analytical thinking (logic, math etc).\u000aThere is no additional essay question for this seminar.
